[1/112] P5 English EOY Rosyth 2025 — Q4  Primary 5  (12.7s)
============================================================
STEM: Most of the students , except for Judy, ___ going to watch the fireworks this weekend.
  (1) is
  (2) are
  (3) was
  (4) were
ANSWER: 2

ELABORATION (601 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement** and **verb tense**.

The main **subject** is "Most of the students", which is **plural**. Phrases between commas like "except for Judy" do not change the **subject**, and "this weekend" means we need a **present tense** verb for a future plan, making option **(2)** correct.

**(1)** fails due to a mismatched **subject** because "**is**" is **singular**.
**(3)** fails due to a mismatched **subject** and wrong **tense** because "**was**" is **singular** and **past tense**.
**(4)** fails due to the wrong **tense** because "**were**" is **past tense**.

