[2/112] P5 English EOY Rosyth 2025 — Q5  Primary 5  (19.3s)
============================================================
STEM: "I think either Sue or her group members ___ the first-aid kits," the class monitor told his teacher.
  (1) take
  (2) takes
  (3) has taken
  (4) have taken
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (688 chars):
The rule tested is **subject-verb agreement** with "**either... or**", where the **verb** must agree with the **subject** closest to the blank.

In this sentence, the closest **subject** is the **plural** noun "group members", so we need a **plural verb**. We also need the **present perfect tense** because the action was completed but is relevant now, making **(4)** correct!

Why the wrong options fail:
**(1)** fails because "**take**" uses the **simple present tense** for habits, not completed actions.
**(2)** fails because "**takes**" is a **singular verb** and the wrong **tense**.
**(3)** fails because "**has taken**" is a **singular verb**, mismatching our **plural subject**.

