============================================================
STEM: The basketball school team witnessed ___ improvement in their teamwork after their coach had given them a pep talk.
  (1) few
  (2) little
  (3) many
  (4) much
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (667 chars):
This question tests the use of **quantifiers** with **countable** and **uncountable nouns**.

The word "improvement" here is an **uncountable noun**. Since the team got a lot better after an encouraging pep talk, we use "**much**" to show a large amount of progress, making **(4)** the correct answer!

Here is why the other options are wrong:
**(1)** "few" is the wrong quantifier because it is used for a small number of **countable nouns**.
**(2)** "little" has the wrong meaning because it means almost zero progress, which does not fit after a helpful pep talk.
**(3)** "many" is the wrong quantifier because it is used for a large number of **countable nouns**.

