============================================================
STEM: Dave and Tom can get along very well with each other ___ they have many differences in their interests.
  (1) so
  (2) since
  (3) though
  (4) because
ANSWER: 3

ELABORATION (604 chars):
This question tests your understanding of **conjunctions of contrast**.

We use **though** to connect two ideas that contrast or surprise us. It is the correct answer because getting along well is a surprising result when two people have very different interests!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** "so" is a **conjunction of result**, which creates the wrong logical relationship here.
**(2)** "since" is a **conjunction of reason**, which doesn't fit these opposing ideas.
**(4)** "because" is also a **conjunction of reason**, but having different interests is not the reason they get along.

